@andrey-me  @markusweimer  I have addressed your comments.

@markusweimer I have introduced another layer of MutableMetrics on top of the APIs that has indexers and operator overloads we discussed. Can you have an overall look and see if it looks ok? If yes then I will introduce relevant tests also for that layer. Alternatively, we can split them in two JIRAs.

Also tried addressing your comments regarding using Rx interfaces.

I've made a pass. Since this PR touches the core REEF runtime, I view it as quite risky and suggest the following to merge this.

We should consider adding unit tests to ensure that `Closing` state works as expected. 
@sanha Can you please have a look into this ?

@tcNickolas  We should test this PR on a real cluster (to which I don't have access right now).

PS The original motivation for [REEF-832](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-832) was to clean up the state handling code. Is it supposed to happen with this PR or should we file a separate issue for this ?

